comment.text: This translation key is used for the title of a download app button on an Android device, prompting users to access organization documents on Google Play. The key appears in a mobile app and will be displayed on screen as part of a UI element.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase 'Get ... Documents' is best translated as 'Yüklə...' instead of 'Əldə edin...'. 'Əldə edin' is a more formal phrase, while 'Yüklə' is more common and natural for downloading apps or documents.

The Czech translation 'Získat dokumenty {{organizationName}} na Google Play' is a literal translation that doesn't sound natural in Czech. It's missing a preposition or connector to make it flow better. A more natural phrasing would imply retrieving documents *from* a specific source.
The phrase "en el Google Play" is not the most natural way to say "on Google Play" in Spanish. It implies being inside Google Play.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Obtener {{organizationName}} Documents en Google Play Store

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Armenian translation includes 'on Google Play-ում'. It is more natural to say 'Google Play-ում' without the 'on'.

The Lao translation "ຮັບເອົາເອກະສານ {{organizationName}} ຢູ່ Google Play" is a literal translation but doesn't convey the meaning of 'Get' in the context of downloading or accessing documents. A more natural Lao phrasing would be something like 'ດາວໂຫຼດເອກະສານ {{organizationName}} ຈາກ Google Play' or 'ເອກະສານ {{organizationName}} ມີຢູ່ Google Play'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ດາວໂຫຼດເອກະສານ {{organizationName}} ຈາກ Google Play

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation uses "Скачать" which means "Download". While functionally similar to "Get", "Get" often implies retrieval or access rather than solely the act of downloading. "Get" might be more appropriate depending on the intended user action.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using a verb that better reflects the action of accessing documents, such as "Получить" (Poluchit' - Receive) if it fits the context.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Google Play හි {{organizationName}} ලේඛන ලබා ගන්න' while understandable, could be improved to more accurately reflect 'Get {{organizationName}} Documents on Google Play'. 'හි' indicates possession, but in this context, it's more about availability *on* Google Play. A more accurate phrasing would incorporate this.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Google Play යටතේ {{organizationName}} ලේඛන ලබා ගන්න

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The spacing around the variable {{organizationName}} could be improved for readability. While technically correct, it might benefit from a slight adjustment.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Google Play යටතේ {{organizationName}} ලේඛන ලබා ගන්න

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian translation "Набави {{organizationName}} Документа на Google Play-у" is a less natural phrasing. "Набави" implies 'obtain' or 'acquire', which isn't the most fitting verb in this context. A more appropriate verb would convey 'Get' as in 'Download' or 'Find'.

The preposition "на" (on) is followed by the dative case ending "-у" when referring to Google Play. While grammatically correct, it can sound slightly less fluent. Using the locative case would be more common in this context.
The word 'Nabavi' translates to 'Obtain' or 'Get'. While understandable, 'Get' is a more natural and common translation in this context. 'Nabavi' sounds slightly formal or archaic.

The English phrase 'Get' is better translated as '获取' (huòqǔ) or '下载' (xiàzài) to convey the meaning of obtaining or downloading. '在Google Play上下载' is acceptable, but '获取' would be more formal and potentially preferable depending on the context.
